headline: This Stock is the Dow’s Second Worst Performer. It Isn’t Getting Any Better.
summary: While  Nike  isn’t the worst-performing stock in the  this year—  Boeing  has fallen harder—analysts at  J.P. Morgan  fear that another shoe may be yet to drop for the company.  On Monday, the bank’s Matthew Boss and his team cut their target for the stock price to $73 from $77, putting it nearly 7% below the stock’s current price.  It isn’t hard to see why J.P. Morgan is concerned.

headline: Black Friday 2024: here are the winners and losers according to BMO
summary: Investing.com -- Retailers saw a mixed bag of results this Black Friday weekend, as consumer spending remained resilient despite ongoing macroeconomic concerns. However, the gap between winners and losers continues to grow, with notable divergences in how brands performed compared to their initial expectations, BMO note says.
